 docker --version
 checking docker version
 
 
 docker pull imagename----> image pull from docker hub
 
 docker image ---> to display image
 
 docker run ----> image run as a container
 
 docker ps  -----> disply containers are running or not
 
 docke run -d  imagename ----> ditached mode
 
 docker stop container id or container name ----> to stop running container.
 
 docker ps -a -----> to show all containers including stoped containers also
 
 docker start container id ---> to start the container 
 
 docker rm container id ----> to remove container
 
 docker rmi imageid ---> will remove images
 
 docker run -d -pport number:old port number -name new name image name -----> changed the container name.
 
 docker exec -it container id /bin/bash ----> enter into container
 
 env --> to search environment sets.
 
 docker volume ls ---> disply volume
 
 docker run -p ----> it is display port number
 
 docker logs container id ---> to display the logs of container 
 
 docker network ls --> to display list of networks
 
 docker network inspect -----> it will show my network
 
 docker inspect ---> to observe each and every minute point(like watch man)
 
 
 
